  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "While digging through migrations code, we found out that there is the undocumented option `save`. If you set this to `false`, Truffle will omit saving the set migrations on chain. This option should probably be documented on the website and in the Truffle help.\r\n\r\nAdditionally there is a bug with this option. If you pass it as a flag (`--save`) on the command line, it gets parsed as a string and will not work correctly. We should tell yargs that this option is a boolean so that it will get parsed properly and work.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
